th to Mana, and the fact that we use almost all Dot's, Necro's are amazingly mana efficient.  Especially when grouping, and the spells you throw are more for the debuff effects rather than the Dot damage.  In groups, at level 42, my most common spells are still Heart Flutter(16) and Shadow Vortex(20).  Between the 2 it's less than 200 mana, but it's -35 AC and -20 STR to the Mob, making it much easier for the thing to be killed.  If your light on tanks and/or healing, Darkness and Fear.  Either way, it's 2 spells per fight, though Fear may need to be re-cast.  The nice thing is, your usually ready with a full bar of mana when the inevitable bad pull comes down, and you need to burn something to the ground with dd's.  Our DD's may not be the most damaging, but we always end that fight at full heath, and they always hit for their full damage.  If you throw that DD on a mob the party pulled and it's resisted, and the party isn't handling the mob, it's time to run--cause you can't touch it.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>There's your free advice.  Remember, you get what you pay for.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p>--Necridious Darkheart<br>"Know Fear through me, not of me."<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/udorraxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dorraxx</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://drakksnet.homestead.com/files/Ghost.gif height=50 width=60" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font c